ass, which could violate some rules. I wonder if we should delete or replace it while maintaining the one-to-one mapping. The existing placeholder might not be dynamic, and updating it to public could work. But since it's not an active class, perhaps leaving it as is is better. The user specifically wants all top-level classes public.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating package visibility**\\\\n\\\\nI‚Äôm considering whether a top-level package should remain package-private or be made public. I think I need to add an implementation dependency in build.gradle. There's also the possibility that the `org.graalvm.internal.tck` class is exposed by the plugin, but it hasn't been utilized yet. I should inspect the native configuration for dependencies, especially to see if core-impl is pulling anything. Hmm, maybe using Gradle rather than running could be more effective. Is viewing the POM in Maven worthwhile if I can't access the internet? Perhaps I can check the local m2 repository instead?\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_PGmP60QLvbuARTxDSiJJWmi9|fc_0e39a17b4266a3130169f65634b0048193bece7ea111793270\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.jboss.arquillian.core -maxdepth 3 -type f | sort | head -50\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1018, \"output\": 1180, \"cacheRead\": 21504, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 23702, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777751586559, \"responseId\": \"resp_0e39a17b4266a3130169f6562392408193bd5f8c1fdeeeb2de\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_PGmP60QLvbuARTxDSiJJWmi9|fc_0e39a17b4266a3130169f65634b0048193bece7ea111793270\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"(no out