 runtime using a name string, there might be a need for reflection configuration related to SecurityActions. This isn't part of test metadata and may rely on agent captures. I think the agent config might include the method handle for native tests, and it‚Äôs possible the agent tracks reflective method lookups.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented the coverage-focused changes for `org.jboss.arquillian.core.spi.SecurityActions`.\\n\\nChanged files:\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-spi/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_core/arquillian_core_spi/SecurityActionsDynamicAccessTest.java`\\n  - Added dedicated public dynamic-access test class for `SecurityActions`.\\n  - Covers:\\n    - default `ManagerBuilder.create()` path for `SecurityActions.loadClass(...)`\\n    - fallback path when TCCL cannot load `ManagerImpl`\\n    - explicit class-loader `newInstance(...)` path and constructor invocation path\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-spi/1.1.10.Final/build.gradle`\\n  - Added `arquillian-core-impl` test dependency using the same tested `libraryVersion`, needed because `ManagerBuilder` loads `org.jboss.arquillian.core.impl.ManagerImpl`.\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.core/arquillian-core-spi/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_core/arquillian_core_spi/Arquillian_core_spiTest.java`\\n  - Made the existing top-level test class `public` to comply with the task rule.\\n\\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0e39a17b4266a3130169f656bcd10c81939d7c17c63a8bae37\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1276, \"output\": 1013, \"cacheRead\": 35328, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 37617, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"time